The paper deals with image captioning, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves language modeling (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.LG), which are likely sub-categories. The paper discusses the merits of different approaches and combines them to achieve better results, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models using metrics such as BLEU, which is a measure of similarity between texts and falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
